# Mivia Agent Workflows

Use this skill when the task is about workflows driven by `mivia-agent`.

## Read First

- `AGENTS.md`
- `.ai/INDEX.md`
- `mivia-agent.yaml`
- `.ai/workflows/*.yaml`

## Workflow Contract

Treat `mivia-agent` as the runtime boundary. Do not simulate a workflow in chat when the CLI can prove it.

Start with:

```bash
./mivia-agent adapters --repo . --json
./mivia-agent run --repo . --workflow <name> --dry-run --json
```

Run live only after the dry-run resolves the expected producer, reviewer, model, and effort:

```bash
./mivia-agent run --repo . --workflow <name> --json
```

Workflow `artifact` values are logical artifact names such as `bug-audit.md`, not repo output paths. The engine writes them under:

```text
.ai/runs/<run-id>/<step-id>/iter-<nnn>/<artifact>
```

Never commit `.ai/runs/`, `.ai/audit.jsonl`, raw prompts, provider payloads, model transcripts, secrets, or credentials.

## Shipped And Common Workflows

- `research-loop`: a producer creates `research.md`; configured reviewers review it.
- `bug-audit-loop`: a producer creates `bug-audit.md`; configured reviewers review it.
- `crush-research-loop`: if configured by the repo, local Crush/Qwen produces a context artifact and another adapter reviews it.

## Desktop-Agent Rules

Codex, Claude, and generic desktop agents should use this skill for workflow intent. Hooks may remind the agent to use the skill, but hooks should not auto-run long model workflows.

A passing workflow means the artifact was accepted as useful workflow output. It does not approve the repository to merge, release, deploy, push, or skip quality gates.

## Final Report

Report:

- Workflow name.
- Dry-run result.
- Live run result if executed.
- Artifact path under `.ai/runs/...`.
- Whether review consensus passed.
- Residual risk and any not-run reason.
